## 5. Real-Time Data Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Pipeline as AI Backend Pipeline
    participant JSON as market_dashboard_data.json
    participant Frontend as React Dashboard

    Pipeline->>JSON: Writes fresh data after each run
    Frontend->>JSON: Fetches every 10 seconds (Polling)
    JSON-->>Frontend: Returns updated JSON
    Frontend->>Frontend: Updates state → re-renders charts & numbers
    Frontend->>Frontend: AnimatedNumber flashes on changed values
    Note over Frontend: Tab hidden? Polling paused (saves battery)
    Note over Frontend: Tab reopened? Immediate re-fetch
    Note over Frontend: Fetch fails? Red "Connection Lost" banner shown
```

### Why Polling (not WebSockets)?
The AI pipeline runs as a **batch process** (not a streaming server), so data only changes when the Python script completes a new run. Polling every 10 seconds is perfectly matched to this update frequency and requires zero changes to the backend.

